I agree with Aditya's comment in other file that @Bean should not be in @component.

I still find it odd to @Autowired CPSConfiguration when we want to access only properties.

Suggestion: 
------
@Configuration
public class CpsConfiguration {

    @Setter @Getter
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "cps-core")
    @Component
    public static class CPSProperties {

        private String baseUrl;
        private String dmiRegistrationUrl;
        private Credential auth;

        @Getter
        @Setter
        public static class Credential {

            private String username;
            private String password;
        }
    }

    @Bean
    public RestTemplate restTemplate(final RestTemplateBuilder restTemplateBuilder) {
        return restTemplateBuilder.build();
    }
}
-----
This implementation will allow to autowire only CPSProperties in NCMPRestClient.
